🔹 What is Customization?

Customization in ServiceNow means modifying the platform’s existing features, forms, workflows, UI, or functionality to meet specific business requirements.

🔹 Features
Modify forms and fields
Create custom applications
Configure workflows and flows
Customize UI and portals
Add business rules and scripts
🔹 Types of Customization
1. Form Customization
Add, remove, or rearrange fields
Modify sections and layouts
2. UI Customization
Personalize pages and user interface
Configure Workspace and UI Builder
3. Workflow Customization
Create automated processes using Flow Designer
4. Scripting Customization
Use Client Scripts, Business Rules, Script Includes
5. Application Customization
Build applications using App Engine Studio
🔹 Benefits
Aligns platform with business needs
Improves efficiency and productivity
Enhances user experience
Enables process automation
🔹 Example

Customize the Incident Form by:

Adding a new field → Issue Category
Creating a flow for auto-assignment
Showing fields based on conditions
